# Grasshopper Libraries deploy (MetalGH / GHGPUPlugin)

Whenever you finish a successful **`dotnet build`** of **GHGPUPlugin** (any configuration), ensure Rhino 8 Grasshopper has the latest plugin and native pieces.

## What to copy

From the build output directory (e.g. `GHGPUPlugin/bin/Release/net7.0/` or `.../Debug/net7.0/` matching the build you ran):

- `GHGPUPlugin.gha`
- `MetalBridge.dylib` (if present next to the `.gha`)
- `default.metallib` (if present next to the `.gha`)

## Destination (macOS, Rhino 8)

`$HOME/Library/Application Support/McNeel/Rhinoceros/8.0/Plug-ins/Grasshopper (b45a29b1-4343-4035-989e-044e8580d9cf)/Libraries`

If that folder is missing (different Rhino install), report it instead of failing silently.

## When to run deploy

1. **After every `dotnet build`** of this project in agent sessions — the `.csproj` already runs **`DeployToGrasshopperLibraries`** on build; if you only edited files without building, run **`cd GHGPUPlugin && dotnet build -c Release`** (or the same config the user asked for) so deploy runs.
2. **After rebuilding MetalBridge** — rebuild the plugin so `MetalBridge.dylib` / `default.metallib` are copied into the output folder, then build **GHGPUPlugin** again (or copy those two files from `MetalBridge/build/Release/` and `MetalBridge/Kernels/` into **Libraries** alongside the `.gha`).
3. **After any agent change** to **GHGPUPlugin**, **MetalBridge**, or **Shaders** that affects the running plugin — run **`xcodebuild`** (Release) on MetalBridge when `.mm`/`.metal` changed, then **`dotnet build GHGPUPlugin/GHGPUPlugin.csproj -c Release`** so the **Libraries** folder gets a fresh `.gha`, `MetalBridge.dylib`, and `default.metallib`. Do not skip deploy when the user expects to test in Rhino.

## GitHub (push)

When the user asks to update the remote (e.g. “push to GitHub”), or when finishing work that should be shared: **`git add`**, **`git commit`** with a concise message, **`git push origin`** (current branch). Ensure new Metal shaders and native sources are committed so a clean clone can build.

## Quick verify

List the three files in **Libraries** and confirm timestamps match the build you just ran.

Do **not** tell the user to copy manually if you can run the build or `cp` yourself in this environment.
